android.car

类 CarOccupantZoneManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.car.CarManagerBase
      • android.car.CarOccupantZoneManager

  • public class CarOccupantZoneManager
extends CarManagerBase
    API to get information on displays and users in the car.

    From car version CarVersion.VERSION_CODES.UPSIDE_DOWN_CAKE_0, system without the driver zone is allowed and the current user will not be the driver.

        public int getDisplayIdForDriver(int displayType)
        Returns the display id for the driver.

        This method just returns the display id for the requested type. The returned display id may correspond to a private display and the client may not have access to it.

        参数:
        displayType - the display type
        返回:
        the driver's display id or Display#INVALID_DISPLAY when no such display exists or if the driver zone does not exist.

        返回:

        返回:

      • assignProfileUserToOccupantZone

        @Deprecated
public boolean assignProfileUserToOccupantZone(CarOccupantZoneManager.OccupantZoneInfo occupantZone,
                                                            int userId)
        已过时。 Use assignVisibleUserToOccupantZone(OccupantZoneInfo, UserHandle) instead.
        Assigns the given profile userId to the occupantZone. Returns true when the request succeeds.

        Note that only non-driver zone can be assigned with this call. Calling this for driver zone will lead into IllegalArgumentException.

        参数:
        occupantZone - Zone to assign user.
        userId - profile user id to assign. Passing INVALID_USER_ID leads into removing the current user assignment.
        返回:
        true if the request succeeds or if the user is already assigned to the zone.

      • assignVisibleUserToOccupantZone

        public int assignVisibleUserToOccupantZone(CarOccupantZoneManager.OccupantZoneInfo occupantZone,
                                           UserHandle user)
        Assign a visible user, which gets true from (UserManager#isUserVisible(), to the specified occupant zone.

        This API handles occupant zone change.

        This API can take a long time, so it is recommended to call this from non-main thread.

        The return value is USER_ASSIGNMENT_RESULT_OK when the assignment succeeds or if the user is already allocated to the zone. Note that new error code can be added in the future. For now, following error codes will be returned for a Failure:

        • USER_ASSIGNMENT_RESULT_FAIL_NON_VISIBLE_USER for non-visible user.
        • USER_ASSIGNMENT_RESULT_FAIL_ALREADY_ASSIGNED if the user is already assigned to other zone. New error code can be added in future.
        • USER_ASSIGNMENT_RESULT_FAIL_DRIVER_ZONE if non-current user is assigned to the driver zone.

        The system requires one user to have one zone and moving user from one zone to another requires unassigning the zone using unassignOccupantZone(OccupantZoneInfo) first.

        参数:
        occupantZone - the occupant zone to change user allocation
        user - the user to allocate. null user removes the allocation for the zone UserHandle#CURRENT will assign the current user to the zone
        返回:
        Check the above

      • unassignOccupantZone

        public int unassignOccupantZone(CarOccupantZoneManager.OccupantZoneInfo occupantZone)
        Un-assign user from the specified occupant zone. The zone will return INVALID_USER_ID for getUserForOccupant(OccupantZoneInfo) after this call.
        参数:
        occupantZone - Zone to unassign.
        返回:
        USER_ASSIGNMENT_RESULT_OK if the zone is unassigned by the call or was already unassigned. Error code of USER_ASSIGNMENT_RESULT_FAIL_DRIVER_ZONE will be returned if driver zone is asked.

      • registerOccupantZoneConfigChangeListener

        public void registerOccupantZoneConfigChangeListener(CarOccupantZoneManager.OccupantZoneConfigChangeListener listener)
        Registers the listener for occupant zone config change. Registering multiple listeners are allowed.

      • unregisterOccupantZoneConfigChangeListener

        public void unregisterOccupantZoneConfigChangeListener(CarOccupantZoneManager.OccupantZoneConfigChangeListener listener)
        Unregisters the listener. Listeners not registered before will be ignored.

      • getMyOccupantZone

        public CarOccupantZoneManager.OccupantZoneInfo getMyOccupantZone()
        Returns CarOccupantZoneManager.OccupantZoneInfo for the calling process's android user. It will return null if there is no occupant zone assigned for the user.

        When there is no occupant zone allocated for the user, most likely the user is not allowed to run Activity or play audio, which are the main use cases to get the zone. So apps should not try such tasks when null OccupantZoneInfo is returned. There can be an exception for system user running under Headless System User Mode: The system user apps may show UI even if there is no zone allocated.

      • getOccupantZoneForUser

        public CarOccupantZoneManager.OccupantZoneInfo getOccupantZoneForUser(UserHandle user)
        Returns OccupantZoneInfo associated with the given UserHandle. In the case that the user is associated with multiple zones, this API returns the first matched zone.
        参数:
        user - The user to find.
        返回:
        Matching occupant zone or null if the user is not assigned or user has a userId of UserHandle#USER_NULL.

      • getOccupantZone

        public CarOccupantZoneManager.OccupantZoneInfo getOccupantZone(int occupantType,
                                                               int seat)
        Finds OccupantZoneInfo for the given occupant type and seat.

        ForOCCUPANT_TYPE_DRIVER and OCCUPANT_TYPE_FRONT_PASSENGER, seat argument will be ignored.

        参数:
        occupantType - should be one of OCCUPANT_TYPE_DRIVER, OCCUPANT_TYPE_FRONT_PASSENGER, OCCUPANT_TYPE_FRONT_PASSENGER
        seat - Seat of the occupant. This is necessary for OCCUPANT_TYPE_REAR_PASSENGER.
        返回:
        Matching occupant zone or null if such zone does not exist.

      • hasDriverZone

        public boolean hasDriverZone()
        Returns true if the system has a driver zone. It will return false for system with only passenger zones.

        Note that at least one zone must be present and following system configurations are possible:

        • One driver zone only.
        • One driver zone with at least one passenger zone.
        • At least one passenger zone.

      • hasPassengerZones

        public boolean hasPassengerZones()
        Returns true if the system has front or rear passenger zones. Check hasDriverZone() for possible system configurations.

      • onCarDisconnected

        public void onCarDisconnected()
        从类复制的说明: CarManagerBase
        Handle disconnection of car service (=crash). As car service has crashed already, this call should only clean up any listeners / callbacks passed from client. Clearing object passed to car service is not necessary as car service has crashed. Note that Car*Manager will not work any more as all binders are invalid. Client should re-create all Car*Managers when car service is restarted.
        指定者:
        onCarDisconnected 在类中 CarManagerBase

      • getSupportedInputTypes

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> getSupportedInputTypes(CarOccupantZoneManager.OccupantZoneInfo occupantZoneInfo,
                                                                int displayType)
        Returns the supported input types for the occupant zone info and display type passed as the argument.

        It returns an empty list if the input type is unknown. Starting in Android android.os.Build.VERSION_CODES#UPSIDE_DOWN_CAKE, all associated occupant zones and display types in config_occupant_display_mapping must define at least one input type.

        If the display doesn't have any input type associated, then it should return a list containing CarInputManager.INPUT_TYPE_NONE only.

        This is the list of all available input types this method may return:

        • CarInputManager.INPUT_TYPE_ROTARY_NAVIGATION
        • CarInputManager.INPUT_TYPE_ROTARY_VOLUME
        • CarInputManager.INPUT_TYPE_DPAD_KEYS
        • CarInputManager.INPUT_TYPE_NAVIGATE_KEYS
        • CarInputManager.INPUT_TYPE_SYSTEM_NAVIGATE_KEYS
        • CarInputManager.INPUT_TYPE_CUSTOM_INPUT_EVENT
        • CarInputManager.INPUT_TYPE_TOUCH_SCREEN
        • CarInputManager.INPUT_TYPE_NONE
        参数:
        occupantZoneInfo - the occupant zone info of the supported input types to find
        displayType - the display type of the supported input types to find
        返回:
        the supported input types for the occupant zone info and display type passed in as the argument (see the full list of supported input types in the above)
